\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24  (}{\f0\fs24\i1 n\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u257\'61s\u226\'E2}{\f0\fs24 ). vb. }{\f0\fs24\b1 test, try, tempt, put one to the test.}{\f0\fs24  }{\f0\fs24\i1 Describes God putting people to the test or people testing God.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\i1
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 The verb }{\f0\fs24\i1 n\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u257\'61s\u226\'E2}{\f0\fs24  can be used to describe the act of God testing individuals and groups, such as Abraham (Gen 22:1), Israel (in both the wilderness and the promised land; e.g., Exod 15:25; 16:4; Deut 8:2; Judg 3:4), the tribe of Levi (Deut 33:8), Hezekiah (2 Chr 32:31), and a psalmist (Psa 26:2). }
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\ul\ulc0 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s testing has particular purposes: }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 to prevent people from sinning (Exod 20:20b); }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 to see whether they will follow God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s instructions (Exod 16:4); }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 to discover the motives of the heart and to keep his commandments (Deut 8:2; 2 Chr 32:31); }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 to do good in the end to those he tests (Deut 8:16); }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 and to see whether they love him wholeheartedly (Deut 13:4) and whether they will obey the his way (Judg 2:22; 3:4). }
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 The verb }{\f0\fs24\i1 n\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u257\'61s\u226\'E2}{\f0\fs24  also refers on several occasions to Israel putting God to the test during the wilderness journey (e.g., Exod 17:7; Num 14:22; Deut 6:16; Psa 78:18; 95:9). It is used once to describe the occasion of Ahaz testing God (Isa 7:12).}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {\f0\fs24  The verb }{\f0\fs24\i1 n\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u257\'61s\u226\'E2}{\f0\fs24  can also be used in the sense of testing the feasibility of some actions or matters (Deut 4:34; 28:56; Judg 6:39; 1 Sam 17:39; Eccl 7:23).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0  Kim, S. H. (2014). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/lxtheowrdbk?ref=biblio.at%3dTesting%7Cau%3dKim%2c%2520Sun%2520Hee&off=3797&ctx=%D7%A0%D6%B8%D7%A1%D6%B8%D7%94~+(na%CC%84sa%CC%82).+vb.+test%2c+try%2c+tempt%2c+pu"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf5 Testing\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 . D. Mangum, D. R. Brown, R. Klippenstein, & R. Hurst (Eds.), \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 Lexham Theological Wordbook\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 . Bellingham, WA: Lexham Press.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
